HEADWORD: Chartreuse
<hw>Char`treuse"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A Carthusian monastery; esp. <altname>La Grande
Chartreuse</altname>, mother house of the order, in the mountains near
Grenoble, France.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An alcoholic cordial, distilled from aromatic herbs;
-- made at <xex>La Grande Chartreuse</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chartreux</ent>⟦br⟧
